Privacy Policy for Cars vs Angels

Last Updated: May 19th 2025

Introduction
Cars vs Angels ("the Game") is developed and published by Inhumanity studios ("we", "us", "our"). We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring a safe user experience. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our game.

Information We Collect

We may collect the following types of information when you play Cars vs Angels:

Personal Information: We do not collect any personally identifiable information (such as name, email, or address) unless voluntarily provided by you.

Non-Personal Information: We may collect non-identifiable information, including device information (model, OS version), game performance data, crash reports, and anonymous gameplay analytics to improve user experience.

Third-Party Services: The game may use third-party analytics and ad networks, such as Google AdMob, which may collect information to serve personalized ads. Please refer to their privacy policies for more information.

How We Use the Information

We use the collected data to:

Improve game performance and user experience

Analyze gameplay patterns and track game metrics

Display personalized or non-personalized ads, depending on your settings

Sharing Your Information

We do not share your personal information with third parties except for analytics and advertising partners as described.

Data Security

We use industry-standard security measures to protect your data. However, please be aware that no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure.

